cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning, specifically the combination of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) for semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also presents a new learning procedure for maximum likelihood estimation, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and inference, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of non-parametric potentials in the CRF model could also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the application of the model to semantic labeling of body parts in depth images could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
